# MCP Server Bridge

## Purpose

MCP (Model Context Protocol) server stdio expose'uje Open Design state do Claude Code w **client repos** (typically z roduq-web-starter scaffold).

Klient w `roduq-web-starter`/`.claude/settings.json`:

```jsonc
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "roduq-design": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["C:/Users/stefa/GIT/roduq-design-generator-studio/dist/mcp-server.js"],
      "env": { "ROduQ_OUTPUT_DIR": "C:/Users/stefa/.roduq/output" }
    }
  }
}
```

## Tools exposed (3 minimum)

### `get_design_state(clientId: string)`

Returns current artifacts dla client:

```typescript
{
  meta: { generatedAt, skill, variant },
  tokens: { ... },
  sections: { ... },
  content: { ... },
  status: "complete" | "in-progress" | "error"
}
```

### `regenerate_section(clientId: string, sectionId: string, hint?: string)`

Re-runs single section generation z optional hint dla LLM:

```typescript
// Example call:
{
  clientId: "acme-corp",
  sectionId: "hero",
  hint: "Make it more focused na enterprise z social proof"
}
// → updates sections.json + meta.json (regeneratedAt timestamp)
```

### `pick_variant(clientId: string, variantNum: number)`

Updates meta.json z user's variant selection (post multi-variant generation):

```typescript
// Example call:
{ clientId: "acme-corp", variantNum: 2 }
// → meta.json.variant = 2, tokens/sections/content updated do variant 2 versions
```

## Transport: stdio

✅ **Stdio MCP** (standard pattern for Claude Code MCP servers):
```typescript
import { Server } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/index.js";
import { StdioServerTransport } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js";

const server = new Server(
  { name: "roduq-design", version: "1.0.0" },
  { capabilities: { tools: {} } }
);

server.setRequestHandler(/* ListToolsRequest */, async () => ({
  tools: [
    { name: "get_design_state", description: "...", inputSchema: { ... } },
    { name: "regenerate_section", description: "...", inputSchema: { ... } },
    { name: "pick_variant", description: "...", inputSchema: { ... } },
  ],
}));

server.setRequestHandler(/* CallToolRequest */, async (request) => {
  // dispatch do tool handler
});

const transport = new StdioServerTransport();
await server.connect(transport);
```

❌ **HTTP transport** — używamy tylko dla future server-side deployments (out of scope v1).

## File system access

✅ **MCP server reads from `~/.roduq/output/<client-id>/`**:
```typescript
const outputDir = process.env.ROduQ_OUTPUT_DIR ?? path.join(os.homedir(), ".roduq", "output");
const clientDir = path.join(outputDir, clientId);
```

✅ **Atomic reads** — check `.complete` flag exists przed reading:
```typescript
if (!await fileExists(path.join(clientDir, ".complete"))) {
  return { status: "in-progress", message: "Generation nie ukończony" };
}
```

## Schema validation w tools

✅ **Every tool input** validated z Zod:
```typescript
const GetDesignStateInput = z.object({
  clientId: z.string().min(1).regex(/^[a-z0-9-]+$/),
});

const result = GetDesignStateInput.safeParse(request.params.arguments);
if (!result.success) {
  return { error: { code: "INVALID_PARAMS", message: result.error.message } };
}
```

## Error handling

✅ **Structured errors** w MCP responses:
```typescript
{
  content: [{ type: "text", text: "..." }],
  isError: true,
}
```

❌ **NIE throw** w handlers — return structured error response.

## Anti-patterns

❌ **MCP server modyfies state w sister repo** (roduq-web-starter) — read-only z `.roduq/output/`. Updates do meta.json/sections.json zostają w tym repo.

❌ **MCP server runs design generation locally** w Claude Code session — design generation odbywa się w UI Open Design app (Next.js). MCP tylko expose'uje wyniki.

❌ **Synchronous file operations** — wszystko async.

❌ **No tool description** — Claude Code wymaga dla tool discovery.

## Patterns

✅ **Tool dispatcher**:
```typescript
const TOOL_HANDLERS: Record<string, (args: never) => Promise<ToolResult>> = {
  get_design_state: handleGetDesignState,
  regenerate_section: handleRegenerateSection,
  pick_variant: handlePickVariant,
};

server.setRequestHandler(CallToolRequestSchema, async (request) => {
  const handler = TOOL_HANDLERS[request.params.name];
  if (!handler) throw new Error(`Unknown tool: ${request.params.name}`);
  return handler(request.params.arguments);
});
```

✅ **Tool result format**:
```typescript
return {
  content: [
    { type: "text", text: JSON.stringify(designState, null, 2) }
  ],
};
```

## Testing

✅ **Integration test** z MCP SDK client:
```typescript
import { Client } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/client/index.js";

const client = new Client({ name: "test", version: "1.0.0" }, { capabilities: {} });
await client.connect(/* stdio transport spawn'ujący server */);
const result = await client.callTool({ name: "get_design_state", arguments: { clientId: "test" } });
expect(result.content[0].text).toContain("tokens");
```

## Po Phase 6 ukończony ✅

`packages/roduq-mcp-server/` standalone workspace package shipped (15 files, ~1900 LOC).

Architecture decisions implemented:
- **Standalone workspace package** (`packages/roduq-mcp-server/`) z `@roduq/*` scope (distinct od upstream `@open-design/*`)
- **Zod input validation** per tool (NIE jsonschema runtime — schemas/* JSON files separate output concern)
- **MCPServerError** z 9-code enum dla structured error responses
- **stderr logging** dla stdio transport (stdout reserved dla MCP protocol)
- **No daemon integration** w Phase 6 — Phase 7 wires via `apps/daemon` `od mcp` subcommand

Tool implementation status:
- `get_design_state(clientId)` — ✅ fully implemented (file-system read only)
- `pick_variant(clientId, variantNum)` — ✅ fully implemented (atomic promote flow z .complete LAST)
- `regenerate_section(clientId, sectionId, hint?)` — ⚠ interface only (returns NOT_IMPLEMENTED z Phase 7 steps; LLM wiring deferred)

Section locator format: `<page>:<blocks[N]|blockType>` (e.g., `"homepage:hero"`, `"homepage:blocks[2]"`, `"/cennik:pricing"`).

Client integration via `.claude/settings.json`:
```jsonc
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "roduq-design": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["<repo>/packages/roduq-mcp-server/dist/index.js"],
      "env": { "ROduQ_OUTPUT_DIR": "<HOME>/.roduq/output" }
    }
  }
}
```

Tests: 8 Vitest cases (4 reader + 4 writer) covering validation + read flows + promote success + 3 rejection scenarios.

Phase 7 will add e2e MCP integration tests z `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` client + LLM wiring dla regenerate_section.

Lessons learned w `.docs/IMPLEMENTATION.md § Phase 6` (14 items).

